ces into development and infrastructure.&lt;br&gt;• ​Assist in maintaining compliance with security standards and regulatory requirements (e.g., SOC 2, ISO 27001, NIST).&lt;br&gt;• ​Perform security assessments and testing of applications, systems, and cloud environments.&lt;br&gt;• ​Contribute to threat modeling and risk assessments for new projects and technologies.&lt;br&gt;• ​Create and maintain security documentation, runbooks, and knowledge bases.&lt;br&gt;• ​Provide guidance and mentorship to junior engineers.&lt;br&gt;• ​Stay current on emerging security threats, tools, and technologies. ​&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;• ​Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Cybersecurity, Engineering, or related field; equivalent experience considered.&lt;br&gt;• ​4–6 years of experience in security engineering, IT security, or related roles.&lt;br&gt;• ​Strong understanding of network, application, and cloud security principles.&lt;br&gt;• ​Experience with security tools such as SIEM, IDS/IPS, vulnerability scanners, and endpoint protection.&lt;br&gt;• ​Knowledge of cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure) and security services.&lt;br&gt;• ​Familiarity with compliance and security frameworks (NIST, ISO 27001, SOC 2, CIS).&lt;br&gt;• ​Scripting or automation experience (Python, Bash, or equivalent) preferred.&lt;br&gt;• ​Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.&lt;br&gt;• ​Good written and verbal communication abilities.&lt;br&gt;• ​Industry certifications such as CISSP, GSEC, or CEH preferred.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
